Date: 4/11/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote:  Leading Dog.- A dog trained to run ahead of a mob of sheep to keep them steady. Sheep drivers always use them; but hill shepherds do not like their dogs to learn to lead, as it is supposed to make them slack in pulling sheep. (C.)
Notes:

